  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="ITA99">
<l>iṟaiyem perumā ṉaruḷeṉ ṟimaiyōr</l>
<l>muṟainiṉṟu moymalar kaṭūva – vaṟaikaḻala</l>
<l>cēvaṭiyāṉ ceṅka ṇeṭiyāṉ kuṟaḷuruvāy</l>
<l>māvaliyai maṇkoṇṭāṉ māl</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>While those who don’t blink stand in order [and] strew [bee-]swarmed blossoms,</l>
<l>saying ‘lord, our great lord, grace [us]’, Māl, the one with red feet</l>
<l>with clinking anklets, the red-eyed Tall one, in the form of a dwarf</l>
<l>took the earth from Māvali.<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">For this type of cleft construction, see note to Po. 36.1, with further parallels in Po. 90.3f and in Pū. 95.1f., Pē. 98.4.</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
